Big Hair}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 : Custom Fractal model. Mids without mud. Revive the 80s metal.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Spawn Nitrous}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Splawn Nitro, KT-88 power tubes, overdrive channel, 100w. Speakers\~ : G12M, G12-65, V30. Stock cabs\~ : 36/37/38/58/60/61/96/101/102/103 (G12M)\~ ; 29/56 (G12-65)\~ ; 41/43/44/47/48/51/53/59/62/63/65/60/70/71/72/108 (V30). Splawn Website\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ All the Splawn tone with more saturation and voiced for a bigger low end and low mids\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Spawn Q-Rod 1st / 2nd / 3rd}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Splawn Quick Rod, 100w, two channels. Channel 2, 1st gear ("Plexi"), 2nd gear ("Hot Rod JCM 800"), 3rd gear ("Super Hot Rod 800"). Speakers\~ : G12M, G12-65, V30. Stock cabs\~ : 36/37/38/58/60/61/96/101/102/103 (G12M)\~ ; 29/56 (G12-65)\~ ; 41/43/44/47/48/51/53/59/62/63/65/60/70/71/72/108 (V30). Splawn website\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ Signature Splawn tone with lots of bite, strong mids and 3 gear versatility\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Suhr Badger 18 / 30}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Suhr Badger, 18w and 30w , EL84. Speakers\~ : V30. Stock cabs\~ : 41/43/44/47/48/51/53/59/62/63/65/60/70/71/72/108 (V30)\~ ; 85 (1xV30). When increasing Gain, turn down Bass. }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ The Master knob is very powerful when it comes to altering the tone of the amp. When you crank it up the mids get much more pronounced and you get a real warm fat singing lead tone. But it still responds incredibly well to the volume knob so when you back that down the highs and lows become more pronounced as it cleans up. When I saw Guthrie use this amp his "clean channel" consisted of using a volume pedal to back off the input and his full volume tone was singing high gain. You can totally do that with this amp model now\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
. Drive it with pedals.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f2
}
