\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Bludotone Ojai}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Speakers\~ : G12-65 or EVM 12L. Stock cabs\~ : 29/56 (G12-65), 8/12/105/106 (EVM), 104 (Classic Lead 80). Both clean and lead modes modeled with preamp boost (PAB) engaged. To disengage PAB change the tonestack type to Skyline. Austin Buddy\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ To get the most range out of this amp, experiment with Master Volume and listen how it interacts with low or high Drive settings, similar to the real amp. The breakup range/tones between is wide and dynamic and can respond to your playing dynamics, getting crunchier as you dig in and cleaner as you play lighter. The amp's Bass response should increase noticeably as you turn up the Master Volume from the default MV position.\~ \'bb. }{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f2
For a super clean sound, use BludoOjai Clean and change to the Skyline tonestack instead of the Default. Set Drive low (below 2) and Master about 3.5, and Master Input Trim turned way down at 0.333 (it will warm up with gain/mids as you approach 1.0), Bright switch on, with Presence knob around 5. At the other end of the spectrum, for endlessly sustaining any note on the Lead amp model, try Drive around 7+ and Master around 7+ with PAB on (= default tonestack). Turn up Input Trims to taste over 1 if you like. You can put a clean boost in front as well to help.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Boutique 1/2}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Matchless Chieftain, a medium-gain amp, thick, yet crisp, with a fair amount of power amp breakup. Boutique 2\~ : same amp with a boost for more gain and high-frequency emphasis. Speakers\~ : G12M plus G12H. Stock cabs\~ : 26/30 (Matchless), 84 (1xG12M). }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Based on a Vox circuit.}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 For more preamp distortion, lower Master and use Drive for Gain.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Buttery}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Budda Twinmaster. Relies mostly on power amp distortion. Speakers\~ : G12M, G12H. Stock cabs\~ : 36/37/38/58/60/61/96/101/102/103 (G12M), 16/34/57/64 (G12H).}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
CarolAnn OD-2}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Carol-Ann OD-2r. Speakers\~ : EVM 12L or Celestion Classic Lead 80. Stock cabs\~ : 8/12/105/106 (EVM), 104 (Classic Lead 80). Designer Alan Phillips\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab The real world speakers of choice are EVM12L in a 1x12 rear ported and 2x12 with Celestion Classic Lead 80's. I found the 12L emulation did a pretty good job. Some of the others sounded so artificial with that model, like a Rockman \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Division13 CJ}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Divided by 13 CJ11. Based on a 1959 tweed Fender amp. Speakers\~ : G12M. Stock cabs\~ : 84 (1xG12M). Divided by 13 website\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ Like a 1959 tweed amp from Fullerton, but instead of the controls being Volume Tone, they are Volume Treble Bass, with more clean headroom, a wider range of usable overdrive (throw in a little EL 34), fuller, tighter low end\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
. Cliff\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ It is a bassy amp. Works best with single coils. You can increase the LOW CUT FREQ to reduce the fuzziness on bass notes but then it won't sound like the real thing\~ \'bb.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Fox ODS I / II}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Fuchs Overdrive Supreme. I\~ : Mid switch On. II\~ : Mid switch off. Speakers\~ : G12-65 or EVM 12L. Stock cabs\~ : 29/56 (G12-65), 8/12/105/106 (EVM).}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Gibtone Scout}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 :  }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Gibson GA17RVT Scout (1964), 17w, two inputs. Speaker: 1x10}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
. }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Stock cabinet suggestions:}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 3/4 (1x10)}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
,  84 (1xG12M). The amp has no tone controls.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
MR Z 38 Sr}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Dr. Z MAZ 38 SR, an amp popular with country and roots players. Speakers\~ : Alnico Blue plus G12H. Stock cabs\~ : 7/11/13/15/20/24/25/28/55/83/93/94 (Alnico)\~ ; 16/34/57/64 (G12H). Dr Z website\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab The 38 has enough clean headroom to make for a great pedal platform and gives up the goods for a great drive sound at reasonable levels. The 38 can deliver mid 60s blackface sounds as well as UK flavored chime \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
. Cliff\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ This amp has no negative feedback (Damping = 0), therefore Presence turns into a Hi-Cut control. Dr. Z is the quintessential country amp\~ \'bb.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Nuclear-Tone}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 : }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Swart Atomic Space Tone. Speaker}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
: G12M}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
. Stock cab : }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
84 (1xG12M)}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 }{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Swart website : }{\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
This amplifier has 20w of twin 6V6 power in high Class A biased AB and brings some of the most soulful, rich, near three-dimensional tone you have ever heard. This has to be one of the most expressive amplifiers made to our knowledge, and we've tried more than a few. TUBE REVERB and TUBE TREMOLO, something virtually nonexistent in today's marketplace, is just part of the picture. Includes a 12" Custom British Vintage Series BV-25m that screams TONE with body and soul;}{\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 This amp has excellent breakup \'bb.}{\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
 }
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
ODS-100 Clean / Lead}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Dumble OD Special, a coveted but rare amp made famous by Robben Ford. Clean\~ : clean channel. Lead\~ : OD channel. Speakers\~ : G12-65, EVM 12L. Stock cabs\~ : 29/56 (G12-65), 8/12/105/106 (EVM). Previous to firmware 10 the ODS models were based on the Bludotone Ojai (now a separate model). The Input Trim parameter can be used to increase or decrease the drive. The tone get brighter as the MV is reduced and vice-versa. }
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Supremo Trem}{\cf1\ul\ulc0\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ }{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
: Supro 1964T. Speakers\~ : 6" oval speaker, 12" or 15" Jensen. Stock cabs\~ : 18/95 (Supro).}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Two Stone J-35}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Two-Rock Jet 35. Modeled in the lead mode with the \'93Bypass\'94 switch engaged. The Bypass switch bypasses the input tone stack to give a more focused lead sound. Speakers\~ : G12-65. Stock cabs\~ : 29/56 (G12-65)\~ ; 8/12/105/106 (EVM). Cliff\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ Very smooth but there's this unique chirp or something that I've never heard in an amp before. When you hit the note there's this blast of high end that rapidly decays so it has an almost vocal quality. The frequency shaping is very different than most other amps. The Two Rock is the most unique amp I've ever modeled. Almost like a violin but with this really cool chirp on the pick attack\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
