\~ : Custom Fractal model based on Peavey EVH 5150. It's an alternative version of PVH 6160 model, more open and less fizzy than the original amp, with a bouncier feel.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
5153 Red}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : EVH 5150 III, made in collaboration with Fender. Lead channel, 100w 6L6 version. Speakers\~ : G12-EVH. Stock cabs\~ : 49/107 or G12Ms / G12Hs. Cliff\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ A 5150 uses a fixed bias with no adjustment. Depending on the tubes used the bias can run from average to cold. The model uses average. Some people like a colder sound. If you prefer your amps biased cold, then reduce the bias parameter to taste\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
