\par \pard\plain \s19\ql\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb0\sa120\ltrpar\cf0\hich\af3\langfe2052\dbch\af4\afs22\lang1025\loch\f3\fs22\lang1036{\cf1\ul\ulc0\b\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
Recto Orange / Red, Vintage / Modern}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\~ : Mesa Boogie's Dual Rectifier, a high-gain masterpiece with crushing power and tighness. Orange and Red channels, Vintage and Modern modes. Speakers\~ : V30. Stock cabs\~ : 41/43/44/47/48/51/53/59/62/63/65/60/70/71/72/108 (V30)\~ ; 104 (Classic Lead 80). V10\~ : }{\cf1\i\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
\'ab\~ Orange Modern and Red Modern models have no negative feedback and therefore the Presence control is a Hi Cut control. The operation of this control is reversed as compared to the actual amp. If the amp\'92s Presence control is fully clockwise the corresponding setting of the model\'92s Hi Cut control is fully ccw. The model\'92s Hi Cut control has about twice the range of the actual amp so fully ccw on the amp is equal to about noon on the model. (\'85) The Modern modes are highly sensitive to MV setting. Higher MV settings result in more midrange focus while lower MV settings produce a more scooped tone. It is recommended to experiment with the MV setting to achieve the desired tone while compensating for the level increase/decrease with the Level control\~ \'bb}{\cf1\dbch\af2\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\loch\f2
.}
